Anonymous Fri 03 Mar 2023 05:48:34 No.54798412 Report
Quoted By: >>54804217
Just finished reading Ninja Fox in New York City.
It's an exceptional piece of work. In particular I'd praise the fight scene in chapter 6 - it was excellently set up, described, and choreographed, particularly the last few hits and finishing blow. Actually felt a rush reading it.
The rest of the story is quite good as well. You spend a lot of time and a good bit of effort letting us into the main character's head, telling us how he feels without letting it be tacky. Alopex's double life is reconciliated well by the side characters, keeping it believable that the same person could lead those two different lives. One thing I feel was glossed over a bit, though, is how she's come to see the world as a humanoid creature from her origins - surely such a massive, massive change of perspective would have been one of the things she'd spend the most time thinking about (and therefore talking about when she starts opening up).
Looking forward to seeing what happens next now. It seems like it's going to become a more action-oriented story, but I hope that isn't going to be all there is, because I also liked how you had the characters bouncing off each other in the more mundane scenes towards the start of the story.
